SIMPLE: single-foot
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Single-foot
<hw>Sin"gle-foot`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An irregular
gait of a horse; -- called also <altname>single-footed pace</altname>.
See <er>Single</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Single-foot</qex> is an irregular pace, rather rare,
distinguished by the posterior extremities moving in the order of a fast
walk, and the anterior extremities in that of a slow trot.</q>
<rj><qau>Stillman (The Horse in Motion.)</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Single-foot</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Single-foot
<hw>Sin"gle-foot`</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To proceed by means of the
single-foot, as a horse or other quadruped.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Sin"gle-foot`er</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>single-handed</ent>⟦br⟧
